# ===========================
# YARP Reverse Proxy Routes
# ===========================
#
# The API Gateway uses YARP to proxy requests to backend services.
# Routes are configured in appsettings.json under "ReverseProxy" section.
#
# Typical routing patterns:
#   /api/blueprints/*    -> Blueprint Service
#   /api/wallets/*       -> Wallet Service
#   /api/registers/*     -> Register Service
#   /api/tenants/*       -> Tenant Service
#   /api/organizations/* -> Tenant Service
#   /api/auth/*          -> Tenant Service
#
# All backend service endpoints are accessible through the gateway.
# See individual service .http files for endpoint details.
#
# ===========================

### Example: Proxied request to Blueprint Service
GET {{Sorcha.ApiGateway_HostAddress}}/api/blueprints
Accept: application/json

###

### Example: Proxied request to Wallet Service
GET {{Sorcha.ApiGateway_HostAddress}}/api/v1/wallets
Accept: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Example: Proxied request to Register Service
GET {{Sorcha.ApiGateway_HostAddress}}/api/registers
Accept: application/json

###

### Example: Proxied request to Tenant Service health
GET {{Sorcha.ApiGateway_HostAddress}}/api/organizations
Accept: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

